heck what happens when TypeORM tries to parse `"conversations"`. In TypeORM, `in
nerJoin` is defined as:\n```typescript\ninnerJoin(entityClass: EntityClassOrSche
ma, alias: string, condition?: string, parameters?: ObjectLiteral): SelectQueryB
uilder<Entity>\ninnerJoin(property: string, alias: string, condition?: string, p
arameters?: ObjectLiteral): SelectQueryBuilder<Entity>\n```\n\nIf the first argu
ment is a string, it\'s treated as a property path. "conversations" is not a val
id property path on `ConversationParticipantEntity`, so TypeORM might throw an e
rror.\n\nActually, looking at the error log again, I don\'t see a TypeORM error 
about invalid property. The only NestJS error is `innerJoin is not a function` w
hich comes from the mock. But I added `innerJoin` to the mock!\n\nWait, let me r
e-read the error log. The `innerJoin is not a function` error appears at the top
